FBIS3-7409 "dreas059_a_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan ROK's Kim, Delegation Conclude Meetings, Visit Trade Insurance Notes Exchanged OW2503034794 Tokyo KYODO in English 0338 GMT 25 Mar 94 OW2503034794 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, March 25 KYODO -- Japan and South Korea exchanged notes in Tokyo on Friday [25 March] to promote mutual cooperation on trade insurance. Japan's Trade Minister Hiroshi Kumagai and his South Korean counterpart Kim chol-su agreed Thursday that the two countries will strive to build cooperative ties in government trade insurance. Under the accord, Japan's Ministry of International Trade and Industry and Korea Export Insurance Corp. will jointly cover trade insurance for projects undertaken by Japanese and South Korean companies in developing countries. The cooperation will also feature regular meetings among insurance experts from the two countries and interchange of information on country risks and other problems involved in projects.
